messages.message:
Hey team, didn't find a better channel but I have a question regarding Instabase modules in Jupyter Notebook:
We have a user testing in their Dev env importing:
```from instabase.content.filehandle import ibfile
(which ended up with error below)
TypeError: __new__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'serialized_options'```
And also
```from instabase.clients_factory_utils.clients_factory import file_client
(which ended up with error below)
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'redis'```
I know we don't have all Instabase modules installed as there can be multiple dependencies. But can anyone suggest about these 2 above?

I have tried on ib.com (http://ib.com), neither modules are available to import.
But in Dogfood, import ib_file as above works fine; import file_client as above lead to the same error for missing redis.
more error details please refer to: https://instabase.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/3345
CC @Naveen @Mohit this is on bofa dev that you might helped building the image
